Labrum usually brown, sometimes dull cream. Scape dark brown to red-brown, with varying amounts of cream ventrally. Flagellum ranging orange-brown to yellow-brown. Tegula red-brown or brown, usually with a cream spot. Basal and medial terga usually black to red-brown. Apical terga usually cream, sometimes red-brown to yellow-brown (
Fig. 9
). Unmarked areas of tibiae dark brown to orange-brown. Trochanter red-brown or orangebrown. Mediotarsus usually dark brown.

Geographic variation. The extent of thorax colour markings in the Western Colour Morph was generally 9– 13 % (
Fig. 10
). Scores of HTW /HBW were generally larger in the more northerly populations of their range.

